* Iron Raptor doesn't catch the glancing optics of the man she loved as her 
mind reeled in the possability of the Arks total destruction, not noticing 
as he slightly approached her as well.
Though, with such responsabilities as she had gone through that day, she 
felt more alone then ever.
She heard Prowl's words and almost winced, realizing the Ark was indeed in 
worse shape then she had first thought.
However preoccupied with the thoughts of the crumbling Autobot shuttle, she 
did notice that he had moved closer and was now attempting to slide an arm 
around her.
Her little punishment for his comment was the last thing on her mind but her 
body stiffened none the less, yet no growl erupted from her throat as she 
simply turned towards the fraimed schematic of the Cybertronian Fire. There 
was far too much on her mind for cuddling now...though she wanted to now 
more then ever.
And at Klusters word of the Ark caving in, her spark sank even more and that 
lonely feeling seemed to grow an inch. In a sigh her shoulders sank, there 
was so much to do in so little time.*
